Sentencas: We report on the performance of thin-film yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) synthesized by atomic layer deposition (ALD) at temperatures of 50-525 degrees C. Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) was used for conductivity measurements.
Titulo: Low-temperature performance of yttria-stabilized zirconia prepared by atomic layer deposition

Sentencas: Relatively high conductivity values were observed in the low-temperature region when compared to reference values of YSZ synthesized by other methods.
Titulo: Low-temperature performance of yttria-stabilized zirconia prepared by atomic layer deposition

Sentencas: To investigate the conduction mechanism, various experimental variables were modified during the electrical measurements, including the ratio of yttria to zirconia in the ALD YSZ films and the atmospheric conditions.
Titulo: Low-temperature performance of yttria-stabilized zirconia prepared by atomic layer deposition

Sentencas: To relate the electrical properties to the structural characteristics, the crystallinity and microstructure were investigated using transmission electron microscopy (TEM) and X-ray diffraction (XRD).
Titulo: Low-temperature performance of yttria-stabilized zirconia prepared by atomic layer deposition

Sentencas: Finally, the suitability of an ALD YSZ membrane as the electrolyte of micro solid oxide fuel cells was evaluated.
Titulo: Low-temperature performance of yttria-stabilized zirconia prepared by atomic layer deposition

Sentencas: An open circuit voltage of almost 1 V and decent power output were successfully measured below 100 degrees C. (C) 2014
Titulo: Low-temperature performance of yttria-stabilized zirconia prepared by atomic layer deposition
